# Scientific Memo Rules

## Purpose

The scientific memo is a human-readable R&D artifact that helps decide whether the INN-disease pair has enough scientific rationale to proceed.

## Required structure

```markdown
---
type: scientific_memo
run_id: ...
inn: ...
disease: ...
status: completed
created_at: ...
source_count: ...
model: ...
prompt_version: ...
---

# Scientific Memo: {INN} / {Disease}

## 1. Executive scientific summary
## 2. Input recap
## 3. Mechanism of action
## 4. Disease biology and pathophysiology
## 5. Mechanistic rationale for this indication
## 6. Evidence from local PDFs
## 7. PubMed evidence
## 8. ClinicalTrials.gov evidence
## 9. FDA evidence
## 10. EMA evidence
## 11. Current standard of care
## 12. Approved therapies and regulatory status
## 13. Clinical pipeline
## 14. Safety and tolerability considerations
## 15. Unmet medical need
## 16. Scientific risks
## 17. Evidence gaps and open questions
## 18. Source table
## 19. Disclaimer
```

## Citation style

```text
[source: PMID_123456]
[source: NCT_01234567]
[source: FDA_NDA_123456]
[source: PDF_source_1_p12_c03]
```

## Tone

Precise, cautious R&D language. No hype. No unsupported conclusions.
Clearly separate: fact, interpretation, hypothesis, missing evidence, next research question.

## Generation

The memo must be generated from validated structured output, not directly from raw LLM text.
